cs.CV, cs.NA, cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.SE

This paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) and hardware accelerators optimized for deep learning, which suggests that it may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of TensorFlow, a popular machine learning framework, which further supports the idea that it belongs to cs.CV. The paper also involves numerical stencils and matrix multiplication, which are common in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and distributed computing (cs.DC), respectively. The use of AI and hardware accelerators also suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the implementation of a novel approach, which may suggest that it belongs to the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
